Yobe State Governor Alhaji Mai Mala Buni has sworn-in the newly appointed Secretary to the State Government Alhaji Baba Mallam Wali and Seven other Permanent Secretaries with a charge to work hard for better progress. Buni while presiding over the swearing-in at the Government House Damaturu said all the appointees are personalities who excel at their various professions in the civil service charging them to consider the oaths of office and oaths of allegiance they have sworn to as another means of setting a value that one must live and exemplify in public service careers. The Governor who emphasized on the need for more sacrifice for progress, said for development to be realistic everyone must remain committed on obligations and official responsibilities. Buni explained that “This is even more urgent right now when we have an array of challenges to meet. More recently, the challenge of the Boko Haram crisis has set back our progress by many years. “It is a crisis that has affected our people in many ways and had sapped the very scarce resources that we could have used in more useful and more impactful ways to improve the living conditions of our people.” Buni added. The Permanent Secretaries sworn and assigned portfolios are Dr. Mustapha Abba Gaidam permanent Secretary Ministry of Transport and Energy, Alhaji Lawan Kolo Permanent Secretary Ministry of Permanent Secretary Political Affairs, Alhaji Kasim Tijjani Kalli Permanent Secretary Ministry of Housing and Urban Development, Alhaji Zanna Ali Ibrahim Permanent Secretary Protocol, Alhaji Yakubu Dokshi Permanent Secretary Ministry of Basic and Secondary Education, Alhaji Abdullahi Musa Shehu Permanent Secretary Establishment and Service Matters and Engr. Usman Ahmed Permanent Secretary Ministry of Water Resources. 